cs.SE, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.PL

The paper discusses a tool that assists developers in finding suitable code snippets by using natural language processing. This tool is specifically designed to integrate into source code editors, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE). The use of natural language processing also suggests a focus on computational linguistics (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The evaluation of the tool involves user ratings, which suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the tool involves the integration of code snippets, which suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL).
